rs%2FWebspaceNotFound%3Fpath%3D%2Fchrisolivola%2Fhome%2Fpublications%2FTodorov%2C%2BOlivola%2C%2BDotsch%2C%2B%2526%2BMende-Siedlecki%2B%282015%29.pdf}}</ref><ref name=ScienceMic2016-02-03>{{cite news|url=http://mic.com/articles/134210/science-says-resting-bitch-face-is-real-and-you-re-probably-judging-people-for-it#.95lEIh3h9|title=Science Says Resting Bitch Face Is Real — And You're Probably Judging People for It|publisher={{tsl|en|Mic (media company)||Mic}}|author=Natasha Noman|date=2016-02-03|access-date=2016-05-09|quote=In short, RBF is when a person's expression unintentionally implies they are "simultaneously bored, mad and skeptical," Jessica Bennett wrote of her own face in a New York Times op-ed on the subject.|archive-date=2020-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205220832/https://www.mic.com/articles/134210/science-says-resting-bitch-face-is-real-and-you-re-probably-judging-people-for-it#.95lEIh3h9|dead-url=no}}</ref>-{zh-cn:信息技术;zh-tw:資訊科技}-科學家也使用了一種[[臉部辨識系統|臉部辨識系統]]對其進行研究，他們發現這種現象是真實存在的，且雖然概念名稱中使用了指女性的單字「[[Bitch|bitch]]」，但其在男性中出現的機率跟女性一樣普遍。<ref>Mazza, Ed. "[http://m.huffpost.com/us/entry/us_56b2d1e0e4b04f9b57d87c44 Science Finds Resting Bitch Face Is Real -- And Men Can Have It, Too] {{Wayback|url=http://m.huffpost.com/us/entry/us_56b2d1e0e4b04f9b57d87c44 |date=20220501033126 }}", ''[[赫芬顿邮报|赫芬顿邮报]]'' (February 4, 2016): "While there has been a certain amount of sexism surrounding resting bitch face -- even the name itself is laced with it -- the computer detected RBF as frequently in men as it did in women."</ref>

== 歷史 ==
《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》作家{{tsl|en|Grant Barrett|格蘭特·巴雷特}}在一份2013年末的新流行單字片語盤點中稱，該片語可追溯到「至少十年」前。<ref name=Nytimes2013-12-22>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/12/22/opinion/sunday/a-wordnado-of-words-in-2013.html|title=A Wordnado of Words in 2013|work=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|author=Grant Barrett|date=2013-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150418092139/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/12/22/opinion/sunday/a-wordnado-of-words-in-2013.html|archive-date=2015-04-18|access-date=2015-08-02|dead-url=no|quote=Dating back at least 10 years as a described concept but popularized in 2013 by a video made by the group Broken People.}}</ref> 

2013年5月22日，喜劇團體Broken People在{{tsl|en|Funny or Die}}網站上傳了一部戲仿{{tsl|en|public service announcement|公共服務宣導}}的影片，標題為「Bitchy Resting Face」（BRF），內容為因{{tsl|en|blank expression|面無表情}}時看起來像在生氣而受困擾者尋求沒有此困擾者的理解。<ref name=YouTubeBitchyRestingFaceVideo>{{cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3v98CPXNiSk|title=Bitchy resting face|publisher=Broken People|date=2013-05-22|access-date=2015-08-02|archive-date=2020-12-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201215061616/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3v98CPXNiSk|dead-url=no}}</ref>

天生臭臉綜合症成為了流行的[[網路迷因|網路迷因]]，以首字母縮寫「RBF」為人熟知。<ref name="Nytimes2015-08-01"/>

==廣泛傳播==
媒體開始廣泛使用「天生臭臉綜合症」這個詞彙。如被《[[柯夢波丹|柯夢波丹]]》和《[[Elle|Elle]]》等針對女性的生活和時尚雜誌使用，也在虛構和非虛構的文學出版作品中出現。<ref name=Cosmopolitan2015-06-04>{{cite news|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/lifestyle/news/a41460/struggles-women-with-resting-bitch-face-understand/|title=13 Struggles Only Women With Resting Bitch Face Understand|work=[[柯夢波丹|Cosmopolitan]]|author=Stephanie Shi|date=2015-06-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930054623/http://www.cosmopolitan.com/lifestyle/news/a41460/struggles-women-with-resting-bitch-face-understand/|archive-date=2015-09-30|access-date=2015-08-02|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=Elle2014-02-05>{{cite news|url=http://www.elle.com/culture/news/a15323/resting-bitch-face-syndrome|title=I won't apologize for my 'bitchy resting face'|work=[[Elle|Elle]]|author=Kristina Rodulfo|date=2014-02-05|archive-url=https://archive.is/20150201210429/http://www.elle.com/culture/news/a15323/resting-bitch-face-syndrome|archive-date=2015-02-01|dead-url=no|accessdate=2021-01-30}}</ref><ref name=Blindsided>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0vnFBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA15|title=Blindsided|publisher=Butterfly Publishing|first=Holly|last=Mortimer|year=2015|page=15|isbn=9781508448983|access-date=2021-01-30|archive-date=2020-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200113014857/https://books.google.com/books?id=0vnFBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA15|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=Chictionary>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iCTnBAAAQBAJ&q=resting+bitch+face&pg=PT22|title=Chic-tionary: The Little Book of Fashion Faux-cabulary|publisher=Skyhorse Publishing|first=Stephanie|last=Simons|location=New York|year=2014|section=2|isbn=9781629145464|access-date=2021-01-30|archive-date=2021-07-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210723145118/https://books.google.com/books?id=iCTnBAAAQBAJ&q=resting+bitch+face&pg=PT22}}</ref><ref name=EOnline2015-08-04>{{cite news|url=http://ca.eonline.com/news/682992/kristen-stewart-responds-to-accusations-that-she-suffers-from-resting-bitch-face-i-actually-smile-a-lot|title=Kristen Stewart Responds to Accusations That She Suffers From Resting Bitch Face: "I Actually Smile a Lot!"|publisher=[[E!|E!]]|author=Zach Johnson|date=2015-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151111180056/http://www.eonline.com/news/682992/kristen-stewart-responds-to-accusations-that-she-suffers-from-resting-bitch-face-i-actually-smile-a-lot|archive-date=2015-11-11|access-date=2015-08-06|dead-url=no|quote=Kristen Stewart may not have a permanent grin on her face, à la Tom Cruise on a worldwide promo tour, but the actress doesn't suffer from resting bitch face, either. In fact, Stewart is tired of people assuming she's always unhappy. "The whole smiling thing is weird because I actually smile a lot," the actress admitted. "I literally want to be like, 'Dude, you would think I was cool if you got to know me.'"}}</ref> 

{{tsl|en|Hadley Freeman|哈德利·弗里曼}}寫道，在Broken People的影片中被使用後，該詞便極大地為人熟知，她也指出影片中描述男性使用的詞「Resting Asshole Face」（RAF）沒有收到同樣多的討論。<ref name=Guardian2013-07-23>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/jul/23/bitchy-resting-face-aimed-women|title=Bitchy resting face: must it be taken so seriously?|first=Hadley|last=Freeman|work=[[衛報|衛報]]|date=2013-07-23|accessdate=2021-01-30|archive-date=2021-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203164434/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/jul/23/bitchy-resting-face-aimed-women|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[纽约大学|纽约大学]]心理學家喬納森·弗里曼（Jonathan Freeman）進行的一項研究顯示，稍微憤怒的面部表情會讓他人覺得你不可靠。<ref name=Quartz2015-09-06>{{cite news|url=http://qz.com/495771/women-with-resting-bitch-face-are-actually-better-communicators/|title=Women with 'resting bitch face' are actually better communicators|work=[[石英财经网|Quartz]]|author=Rene Paulson|date=2015-09-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150907120145/http://qz.com/495771/women-with-resting-bitch-face-are-actually-better-communicators/|archive-date=2015-09-07|access-date=2015-11-12|dead-url=no|quote=Research has shown that people rely heavily on facial expressions and body language. Psychologist Albert Mehrabian (...) conducted famous studies in the 1960s that found that interpreting someone’s communication is based mostly on nonverbal cues, like facial expression, body language and tone. Women confronted by a world that automatically attaches negative attributes to their non-smiling face must quickly learn how to communicate and also hone a finely-tuned awareness of both our own emotions and the emotions of those around us.}}</ref><ref name=SageJournals2015-06-18>{{cite news|title=Static and Dynamic Facial Cues Differentially Affect the Consistency of Social Evaluations|date=2015-06-18|doi=10.1177/0146167215591495}}</ref>

2014年，克洛伊·霍格（Chloé Hogg）在期刊《{{tsl|en|Philological Quarterly|语文学季刊}}》發表的文章中聲稱此現象並不新鮮，並附上[[亚森特·里戈|亚森特·里戈]]所繪的[[路易十四|路易十四]]「天生臭臉」肖像畫。<ref name=PhiloQuarterly>{{cite journal|url=http://search.proquest.com/openview/1c21559c9442a1776b13020a3db72023/1?pq-origsite=gscholar|title=Subject of Passions: Charles Le Brun and the Emotions of Absolutism|journal={{tsl|en|Philological Quarterly|语文学季刊}}|author=Chloé Hogg|date=2014 冬|pages=65–94|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fsearch.proquest.com%2Fopenview%2F1c21559c9442a1776b13020a3db72023%2F1%3Fpq-origsite%3Dgscholar&date=2015-11-11|archive-date=2015-11-11|access-date=2015-08-02|dead-url=no|quote=Hyacinthe Rigaud's famous portrait of Louis XIV depicts the absolute monarch's absolute physiognomic control as part of the attributes of royalty-what I'm tempted to call, in contemporary emotional parlance, Louis XIV's ''"bitchy resting face"''.}}</ref>天生臭臉綜合症在兇猛的程度上可能差異極大。

